				<skos:prefLabel xml:lang="en">Oakum</skos:prefLabel>
				<skos:scopeNote xml:lang="en">Tarred hemp or manila fibres used for caulking the seams of the decks and sides of a wooden vessel to make it watertight. Oakum is usually made by unpicking old ropes.</skos:scopeNote>
